						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Broken slab lying near the well called Ūra-bhāvi.</hi></p>						

						<p>12th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>The record in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">12th Century A.D.,</hi> seems to register gifts of land as <hi rend="italic">bhaṭṭa-vṛitti</hi> for teaching Nyāsa, Prabhākara, Vēdānta, Ṛigvēda, Purāṇa, etc., and also gifts for dancing girls, drummers and others. The beginning and the end are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
